  "prompt": "What is necessary to be considered a combat veteran?",
  "response": "To be considered a combat veteran, generally, an individual must have:\n\n1. Served in the armed forces during a period of war or military conflict\n\n2. Been deployed to a combat zone\n\n3. Engaged in direct combat or been present in an area with imminent danger\n\nSpecific criteria can vary between branches of service and depend on factors such as:\n- Receiving combat-related awards (like Combat Infantry Badge)\n- Being in an area that qualifies as a combat zone\n- Participating in military operations with potential for hostile fire\n- Receiving hostile fire or imminent danger pay\n\nThe Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) has specific definitions that can determine combat veteran status for benefits and services.\n\nUltimately, official military records and documentation are used to verify combat veteran status.",
